Thx @DrPhil! @Pfizer Chief Medical Officer Freda Lewis-Hall MD checking in. Looking forward to a great discussion #cancerandcareers
A1: A @Pfizer & @CancerandCareer survey found 77% of working women w/ #breastcancer felt working aided in recovery #cancerandcareers (1/2)
A1: And 92% of healthcare professionals surveyed agreed #cancerandcareers (2/2) http://t.co/tEZIVQmOM4
@CancerAndCareer A1: Women w/ #metastatic #breastcancer reported the desire to feel normal at even higher rates #cancerandcareers
A2: You’re right @DrPhil. Our survey also showed that 48% felt managing the disease & treatments posed challenges #cancerandcareers (1/2)
A2: Many indicated managing treatment led to extra days off, a reduced schedule, paid/unpaid leaves or resignation #cancerandcareers (2/2)
A4: Talk to your doctor & know the facts – how treatment will affect your work & how your work will affect treatment #cancerandcareers (1/4)
A4: Seek support – Support groups & patient navigators can help guide you through treatment http://t.co/WjgOFOs3Zm   #cancerandcareers (3/4)
A4: This can help you create a plan that can keep your career going. #cancerandcareers (2/4)
A4: Don’t be afraid to ask for help –  Family, friends & co-workers are usually happy to help w/tasks & errands #cancerandcareers (4/4)
Thx @DrPhil for hosting & to all for the insights! For more information & links, visit http://t.co/WiX9zhzOTd #cancerandcareers
